Again though the game is in Beta, and if I you I would try to find constructive threads written by beta testers, not read a single negative post, instead of the beta players, the kiss asses who get into beta, power lvl then say it sucks because items a b and c are not instituted and because the graphics aren't as polished and they can't camp uber_item_02, etc...  <br>
I am just excited about it because its designed to cater more to casual play than power gamers, they know where the bulk of their players base comes from, and its not from people with 22 hours a day to play, which is why the xp system is the way it is, lvls 1-20 are for learning the game and gaining power to survive a few rounds of pvp combat, lvls 20-30 are there to introduce you to rvr and 30-50 are very slow in lvling and are where you are watching your back every second to make sure some other realm isn't walking through your zone trying to kick your ass.<br>
there is also a bigger difference in power from a lvl 20 and a lvl 30 than a lvl 30 and a lvl 40, that and a lvl 35 warrior that spends their time lvling and doing RvR combat will have enhanced abilities and has a good chance of beating the tar out of a lvl 40 warrior that only lvls and doesn't do RvR.<br>
Everything here is gleaned from dev posts and a few people I know in beta.<br>
